thor_association": "NONE", "sub_issues_summary": {"total": 0, "completed": 0, "percent_completed": 0}, "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "Really love the project and have it up and running on a TTGO board with display.\r\n\r\nThe issue I've got is that I can't use the display and an externally connected SPI thermocouple at the same time.\r\n\r\n```\r\nimport display\r\nfrom machine import SPI\r\nhspi = SPI(spihost=SPI.HSPI, sck=25, mosi=33, miso=27, cs=26)\r\ntft = display.TFT()\r\ntft.init(tft.ST7789,bgr=False,rot=tft.LANDSCAPE, miso=17,backl_pin=4,backl_on=1, mosi=19, clk=18, cs=5, dc=16, splash=False)\r\n```\r\n\r\nWhichever is initialised first seems to have exclusive use of HSPI.\r\n\r\nIn the example above, any attempt to access the tft results in clocking on pin 25.\r\n\r\nIf I init the TFT first then SPI, the display works fine, but a hspi read does not produce any clock signal on pin 25.  (The chip select does assert, though).\r\n\r\nI can deinit one and init the other and use them one at a time, but really the chip select should do that for me.", "reactions": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/loboris/MicroPython_ESP32_psRAM_LoBo/issues/340/reactions", "total_count": 0, "+1": 0, "-1": 0, "laugh": 0, "hooray": 0, "confused": 0, "heart": 0, "rocket": 0, "eyes": 0}, "timeline_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/loboris/MicroPython_ESP32_psRAM_LoBo/issues/340/timeline", "performed_via_github_app": null, "state_reason": "completed", "score": 1.0}]}